headline.main: STAT E AFFAIRS.; RUMORED NOMINATIONS. Passage of the Temperance Bill in the Assembly. CITY APPOINTMENTS.

docs.lead_paragraph: There is more than a crowd here in Albany--there is a jam. Some days since the Canal Board were so verdant as to make announcoment that on the 21st of February they would proceed to receive, consider and cetermine the petitions and prayers of those desirrous of serving the State as Superintendents of Canals, Collectors of Canal Tolls, and the Inspectors of Canal boats, and Weighmasters.

headline.main: FROM WASHINGTON.; The Passenger Bill-Vindication of Senator Fish-Senators and the New-York Times' Opinions-European Manovres-Naval Bitterness.

docs.lead_paragraph: The speech which Senator BENJAMIN made to-day, in defence of Hon. HAMILTON FISH, from the charge of duplicity preferred at the Meeting of New-York Merchants and Shippers, was as creditable to his own head and heart as it must be satisfactory to the friends of the absent Senator.

headline.main: ONE WEEK LATER FROM EUROPE.; Cardigan and Napier---Their Festival Speches. NEWS FROM THE CRIMEA. GREAT SPEECH OF LORD DERBY. The Markets--Cotton Steady--Grain Dull--The Funds Oil. SORTIE ON THE FRENCH LINE. TURKS WANT PEACE. MEETING AMONG FRENCH TROOPS. NEWCASTLE SUPERSEDED. ARRIVAL OF THE STEAMER BALTIC. Aberdeen and Russell Out. THE BRITISH MINISTRY FORMED. PALMERSTON PREMIER. LORD PANMURE SECRETARY OF WAR. LORD GRANVILLE PRESIDENT OF COUNCIL. Lansdowne, Gladstone, Clarendon, Herbert Grey, and Graham Retained.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Uniled States Mail steamer Baltic, Capt. CoMsTocK, from Liverpool about 1 o'clock afternoon of Saturday the 10th, arrived at 12 o'clock P. M. yesterday. The Baltic arrived out at 2i o'clock afternoon of Monday, Fcb. 5. The Asia sailed for Halifax on the. 3d.
